fun main(){

    print("Hello, Meesho")

}

Hello, Meesho

In kotlin, the entryPoint is main() function. 
- Before Kotlin V1.3, you need to specify the parameters inside main() function
- Semicolon is optional 
- If you don't give return type then it will return nothing

Same main() function before V1.3, it was important to pass the parameter as Array<String>

fun main(arr : Array<String>){
  
    print("Hello, Meesho")
    
}
